{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh couscous and oil into it. Place bowl onto work surface and just cover couscous with boiling water. Cover and set aside for 5-10 minutes to absorb. Meanwhile, proceed with recipe.","Place ginger, onion, carrot and green capsicum into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add apricots, raisins, cashews, chickpeas and curry powder and combine <b>15 sec\/\/speed 2<b>.","Fluff couscous with a fork to separate grains, then add carrot mixture to couscous and stir to combine. Garnish with coriander before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g couscous","40 g olive oil","boiling water","1 piece fresh ginger (3-4 cm), peeled and cut into pieces","30 g red onion (approx. ¼ onion), cut into pieces","120 g carrot, cut into pieces","½ green capsicum, cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","50 g dried apricots, cut into pieces (1 cm)","50 g raisins","50 g raw cashews","400 g canned chickpeas, rinsed and drained (approx. 250 g after draining)","1 tbsp curry powder","2 - 3 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only, roughly chopped, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r154190","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-8GQ3Buw6LPs\/XZautCjr3JI\/AAAAAAAAhmg\/PVZgLkwUVWACQJ5jsVcpHrpxzgOvaa8hQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_-RcB17UqkOdla407.png","title":"Curried couscous, carrot and chickpea salad","publishedAt":"2017-09-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10.1 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"43.6 g","calories":"1414 kJ \/ 336 kcal"},"usefulItems":"kitchen towel, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl","basicInfo":["easy","10m","15m","6 portions"]}